data.reasoningText:
Now I see it. The `TestMethodAttribute` constructor in MSTest 4.2.2 only takes `callerFilePath` and `callerLineNumber` — no `displayName` parameter. The `DisplayName` is set as a property instead.

So the fix for the custom attribute is:

```csharp
public CategorizedTestMethodAttribute(
    string category,
    [CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "",
    [CallerLineNumber] int callerLineNumber = -1)
    : base(callerFilePath, callerLineNumber)
{
    Category = category;


}
```

Closing the constructor...

